                "{@b Choice.} Whenever you encounter a meaningful choice of direction, you can spend a moment observing your surroundings. Choose one of the following traits, the DM reveals which of the routes forward most fits that criteria: safest, fastest, most direct, or the path with the most reward.",
                "{@b Navigation.} While you can see the night sky: you and your immediate allies have {@variantrule Advantage|XPHB} on any Wisdom ({@skill Survival}) checks made on your journey, and moving at a fast pace does not affect your Wisdom ({@skill Perception} or {@skill Survival}) or Dexterity ({@skill Stealth}) checks."
