                "All creatures of your choice within the emanation must subtract your spellcasting ability modifier from any damage rolls they make. Additionally, as a {@variantrule Bonus Action}, you can target a creature within the emanation to draw power from them. That creature must make a Constitution saving throw. On a failed save, they take {@damage 4d10} radiant or necrotic damage (your choice) and become {@condition Silenced|Starlight} until the start of your next turn, taking half as much damage only on a successful one. You gain temporary hit points equal to the amount of damage dealt."
